blueprint:
  name: "🌧️ Weather Condition Alert"
  description: |
    ## 🌦️ Description

    This blueprint monitors the **hourly weather forecast** for the next _N_ hours
    and raises an alert when selected conditions (rain, snow, hail, exceptional, etc.)
    are expected for at least a minimum number of hours within that window.

    Instead of hard-coding notifications, it:

    - Toggles an **input_boolean** helper ON/OFF to indicate whether an alert is active.
    - Writes a **human-friendly message** into an **input_text** helper, for example:
      - `Snow expected between 10:00 PM and 11:00 PM (within the next 6 hours).`
      - `Rain expected between 3:00 PM and 5:00 PM (within the next 12 hours).`
      - For **exceptional** conditions, it will tell you to check your local weather source.

    Optionally, it can also:

    - Send a **mobile notification** to Home Assistant companion app devices,
      with quiet hours and basic spam protection (only on state change).
    - Log helpful debug messages so you can see exactly what it did.

    <details><summary><b>How it works</b> ⛈️</summary>
    <p></p>
    <ol>
      <li>Runs on a schedule you choose (e.g. every 15 / 30 / 60 minutes, up to 12 hours).</li>
      <li>Calls <code>weather.get_forecasts</code> with <code>type: hourly</code> for your
          selected weather entity (for example <code>weather.home</code>).</li>
      <li>Looks ahead for the next <strong>N hours</strong> and filters hours whose
          <code>condition</code> matches any of your selected types, such as:
          <code>snowy</code>, <code>snowy-rainy</code>, <code>rainy</code>,
          <code>pouring</code>, <code>hail</code>, <code>exceptional</code>, etc.</li>
      <li>Counts how many of those matching hours are found:
        <ul>
          <li>If the count is <strong>at least the minimum threshold</strong> you configured:
            <ul>
              <li>Turns the boolean helper <strong>ON</strong>.</li>
              <li>Writes a message into the text helper describing what is expected and
                  roughly <strong>between which local times</strong> it occurs.</li>
              <li>(If mobile alerts are enabled and it’s not quiet hours) sends a notification.</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>If no hours match:
            <ul>
              <li>Turns the boolean helper <strong>OFF</strong>.</li>
              <li>Clears the text helper.</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ol>
    </details>

    <details><summary><b>Recommended use cases</b> 🌧️</summary>
    <p></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Showing a <strong>“Snow / Rain Alert” card</strong> on a dashboard using:
        <ul>
          <li><code>input_boolean</code> for visibility / state</li>
          <li><code>input_text</code> for the message body</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Triggering other automations when precipitation is expected, for example:
        <ul>
          <li>TTS or speaker announcements</li>
          <li>Adjusting heating / blinds / exterior lighting</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Getting <strong>phone alerts</strong> for incoming snow, rain, hail, or
          exceptional conditions while still respecting quiet hours.</li>
      <li>Using the boolean as a simple condition in other
          <strong>weather-aware</strong> automations.</li>
    </ul>
    </details>

    <details><summary><b>Debugging tips</b> 🛠️</summary>
    <p></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Turn <strong>Debug logging</strong> to “On” in the blueprint inputs.</li>
      <li>Use <strong>Logbook</strong> and filter by:
        <ul>
          <li>Your weather entity (e.g. <code>weather.home</code>), or</li>
          <li>Text like <code>Weather Condition Alert</code>.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Look for messages such as:
        <ul>
          <li><code>Alert ACTIVE: found X matching hour(s)…</code></li>
          <li><code>Alert CLEARED: no matching hours in lookahead window.</code></li>
          <li><code>Interval check skipped: current time does not align with selected frequency.</code></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Use <strong>Settings → Automations &amp; Scenes → [this automation] → Trace</strong> to inspect:
        <ul>
          <li>The forecast data used for that run.</li>
          <li>Which hours matched your selected conditions.</li>
          <li>Why the boolean/message did or did not change.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
    </details>

    ---

    **Author:** CraveVox  
    **Last updated:** 2025-12-07

  domain: automation
  author: CraveVox
  homeassistant:
    min_version: "2024.6.0"

  input:
    weather_section:
      name: Weather source & window
      icon: mdi:weather-cloudy-clock
      input:
        weather_entity:
          name: Weather entity
          description: >
            The weather entity to use for the hourly forecast (e.g. weather.home).
          selector:
            entity:
              multiple: false
              filter:
                - domain: weather

        hours_to_check:
          name: Hours to check ahead
          description: >
            Number of hours ahead to scan in the hourly forecast. If your weather
            provider returns fewer hours than this, only the available hours will
            be used.
          default: 12
          selector:
            number:
              min: 1
              max: 48
              step: 1
              mode: slider

        include_horizon_suffix:
          name: Include “in the next N hours” in message
          description: >
            When enabled, the alert message will end with “in the next N hours”.
          default: true
          selector:
            boolean: {}

    conditions_section:
      name: Conditions & threshold
      icon: mdi:weather-pouring
      input:
        weather_conditions:
          name: Conditions to alert on
          description: >
            Select one or more weather conditions that should trigger an alert.
            Common examples: rainy, pouring, lightning-rainy, snowy, snowy-rainy.
            The “exceptional” condition is used by some integrations for severe
            or unusual events that don’t fit standard conditions.
          default:
            - rainy
            - pouring
            - lightning-rainy
            - snowy
            - snowy-rainy
          selector:
            select:
              multiple: true
              mode: dropdown
              options:
                - sunny
                - partlycloudy
                - cloudy
                - rainy
                - pouring
                - lightning
                - lightning-rainy
                - snowy
                - snowy-rainy
                - hail
                - fog
                - windy
                - windy-variant
                - exceptional

        min_matching_hours:
          name: Minimum matching hours to alert
          description: >
            Minimum number of hours within the window that must match the selected
            conditions before an alert is raised. Hours do not need to be consecutive.
          default: 1
          selector:
            number:
              min: 1
              max: 48
              step: 1
              mode: slider

    helpers_section:
      name: Alert helpers
      icon: mdi:alarm-light-outline
      description: >
        These helpers drive your dashboards. The boolean turns on when an alert
        is active and off when it clears. The text holds the human-readable
        alert message. If you create multiple automations from this blueprint,
        use separate helpers for each instance.
      input:
        alert_boolean:
          name: Alert boolean helper
          description: >
            Input boolean that will be turned on when matching conditions are
            detected and turned off when they clear.
          selector:
            entity:
              multiple: false
              filter:
                - domain: input_boolean

        alert_message:
          name: Alert message helper
          description: >
            Input text that will contain the generated alert message
            (e.g. “Snow Notice! Snow expected between 3:00 PM and 6:00 PM in the
            next 12 hours.”).
          selector:
            entity:
              multiple: false
              filter:
                - domain: input_text

    schedule_section:
      name: Check frequency
      icon: mdi:clock-outline
      input:
        check_interval:
          name: Check interval
          description: >
            How often to actually run the forecast check. The automation wakes
            every 15 minutes but only does the real work at the interval you
            select here.
          default: "30"
          selector:
            select:
              options:
                - label: Every 15 minutes
                  value: "15"
                - label: Every 30 minutes
                  value: "30"
                - label: Every 1 hour
                  value: "60"
                - label: Every 2 hours
                  value: "120"
                - label: Every 3 hours
                  value: "180"
                - label: Every 4 hours
                  value: "240"
                - label: Every 5 hours
                  value: "300"
                - label: Every 6 hours
                  value: "360"
                - label: Every 12 hours
                  value: "720"

    mobile_section:
      name: 📱 Mobile notifications (optional)
      icon: mdi:cellphone
      collapsed: true
      description: >
        Optional push notifications via the Home Assistant Companion app.
        Notifications are only sent when the alert changes from off to on, and
        only within the configured notification time window below.
      input:
        send_mobile_notifications:
          name: Send mobile notifications
          description: >
            If enabled, a notification will be sent to the selected mobile_app
            devices whenever an alert is raised (on state change from off to on).
          default: false
          selector:
            boolean: {}

        notification_title:
          name: Notification title
          description: >
            Title used for mobile notifications. Default is “Weather Alert”.
          default: Weather Alert
          selector:
            text: {}

        mobile_devices:
          name: Mobile devices (optional)
          description: >
            One or more Home Assistant Companion app devices (mobile_app
            integration) to send alerts to. Only used if "Send mobile
            notifications" is enabled.
          default: []
          selector:
            device:
              multiple: true
              filter:
                - integration: mobile_app

        notify_start_time:
          name: Earliest notification time
          description: >
            Earliest time of day when mobile notifications are allowed
            (local time). Outside this window, helpers still update but no
            notifications are sent.
          default: "07:00:00"
          selector:
            time: {}

        notify_end_time:
          name: Latest notification time
          description: >
            Latest time of day when mobile notifications are allowed
            (local time). If the end time is earlier than the start time, the
            window is treated as wrapping over midnight.
          default: "22:00:00"
          selector:
            time: {}

    debug_section:
      name: 🧪 Debug (optional)
      icon: mdi:bug
      collapsed: true
      input:
        enable_debug:
          name: Enable debug logging
          description: >
            If enabled, writes summary entries to the Logbook for each relevant
            run, indicating whether the alert was triggered, cleared, skipped
            due to interval, or skipped due to missing forecast data.
          default: false
          selector:
            boolean: {}

mode: single

triggers:
  - trigger: time_pattern
    minutes: "/15"

conditions: []

actions:
  - variables:
      check_interval: !input check_interval
      interval_minutes: "{{ check_interval | int }}"
      debug_enabled: !input enable_debug
      minutes_since_midnight: "{{ now().hour * 60 + now().minute }}"
      run_this_cycle: >-
        {% if interval_minutes <= 0 %}
          false
        {% else %}
          {{ (minutes_since_midnight % interval_minutes) == 0 }}
        {% endif %}

  - choose:
      - conditions:
          - condition: template
            value_template: "{{ run_this_cycle }}"
        sequence:
          # Only runs when we're on a matching interval
          - action: weather.get_forecasts
            target:
              entity_id: !input weather_entity
            data:
              type: hourly
            response_variable: forecasts

          - variables:
              conds: !input weather_conditions
              hours_to_check: !input hours_to_check
              min_matching_hours: !input min_matching_hours
              include_horizon_suffix: !input include_horizon_suffix
              alert_boolean_entity: !input alert_boolean
              alert_message_entity: !input alert_message
              send_mobile: !input send_mobile_notifications
              mobile_devices_var: !input mobile_devices
              notify_start_time: !input notify_start_time
              notify_end_time: !input notify_end_time

              merged: "{{ merge_response(forecasts) }}"
              hourly: >
                {% set h = merged %}
                {{ h[:hours_to_check] if h is not none else [] }}

              matching_hours: >
                {{ hourly | selectattr('condition', 'in', conds) | list }}

              matching_count: "{{ matching_hours | length }}"

              first_match: "{{ matching_hours[0] if matching_count|int > 0 else none }}"
              last_match: "{{ matching_hours[-1] if matching_count|int > 1 else first_match }}"

              alert_current_state: >
                {{ states(alert_boolean_entity) if alert_boolean_entity is not none else 'unknown' }}

          - choose:
              # 1) Forecast data present AND enough matching hours → ACTIVATE alert
              - conditions:
                  - condition: template
                    value_template: >
                      {{ (hourly | length > 0) and (matching_count | int >= min_matching_hours | int) }}
                sequence:
                  # Build the alert message text
                  - variables:
                      alert_message_text: >-
                        {% if first_match %}
                          {% set cond = first_match.condition %}
                          {% set dt_start = as_datetime(first_match.datetime) | as_local %}
                          {% set dt_end = as_datetime(last_match.datetime) | as_local %}
                          {% set start_time = dt_start.strftime('%-I:%M %p') %}
                          {% set end_time = dt_end.strftime('%-I:%M %p') %}
                          {% if cond == 'exceptional' %}
                            {% set kind = 'Exceptional weather' %}
                          {% elif 'snow' in cond and 'rain' in cond %}
                            {% set kind = 'Snow and rain' %}
                          {% elif 'snow' in cond %}
                            {% set kind = 'Snow' %}
                          {% elif 'rain' in cond %}
                            {% set kind = 'Rain' %}
                          {% elif cond == 'hail' %}
                            {% set kind = 'Hail' %}
                          {% else %}
                            {% set kind = 'Precipitation' %}
                          {% endif %}
                          {% if include_horizon_suffix %}
                            {% set suffix = ' in the next ' ~ hours_to_check ~ ' hours' %}
                          {% else %}
                            {% set suffix = '' %}
                          {% endif %}
                          {% if cond == 'exceptional' %}
                            {% if matching_count|int == 1 %}
                              Exceptional Weather Notice! Exceptional conditions expected around {{ start_time }}{{ suffix }}. Check your local weather alerts for more details.
                            {% else %}
                              Exceptional Weather Notice! Exceptional conditions expected between {{ start_time }} and {{ end_time }}{{ suffix }}. Check your local weather alerts for more details.
                            {% endif %}
                          {% else %}
                            {% if matching_count|int == 1 %}
                              {{ kind }} Notice! {{ kind }} expected around {{ start_time }}{{ suffix }}.
                            {% else %}
                              {{ kind }} Notice! {{ kind }} expected between {{ start_time }} and {{ end_time }}{{ suffix }}.
                            {% endif %}
                          {% endif %}
                        {% else %}
                          {{ '' }}
                        {% endif %}

                  # Turn on boolean and set message
                  - action: input_boolean.turn_on
                    target:
                      entity_id: !input alert_boolean

                  - action: input_text.set_value
                    target:
                      entity_id: !input alert_message
                    data:
                      value: "{{ alert_message_text }}"

                  # Debug log for active alert
                  - condition: template
                    value_template: "{{ debug_enabled }}"
                  - action: logbook.log
                    data:
                      name: Weather Condition Alert
                      message: >-
                        Alert ACTIVE: {{ matching_count }} matching hour(s) in the next
                        {{ hours_to_check }} hour(s) for conditions {{ conds }}.
                      entity_id: !input weather_entity

                  # Mobile notifications: only on state change (off -> on) and within time window
                  - condition: template
                    value_template: >
                      {{ send_mobile and (mobile_devices_var | length > 0) and alert_current_state != 'on' }}
                  - condition: template
                    value_template: >-
                      {% set now_time = now().time() %}
                      {% set start = strptime(notify_start_time, '%H:%M:%S').time() %}
                      {% set end = strptime(notify_end_time, '%H:%M:%S').time() %}
                      {% if start <= end %}
                        {{ start <= now_time <= end }}
                      {% else %}
                        {{ now_time >= start or now_time <= end }}
                      {% endif %}
                  - repeat:
                      for_each: "{{ mobile_devices_var }}"
                      sequence:
                        - action: notify.mobile_app_{{ device_attr(repeat.item, 'name') | slugify }}
                          data:
                            title: !input notification_title
                            message: "{{ alert_message_text }}"
                          continue_on_error: true


              # 2) Forecast data present BUT below threshold → CLEAR alert
              - conditions:
                  - condition: template
                    value_template: >
                      {{ (hourly | length > 0) and (matching_count | int < min_matching_hours | int) }}
                sequence:
                  - action: input_boolean.turn_off
                    target:
                      entity_id: !input alert_boolean

                  - action: input_text.set_value
                    target:
                      entity_id: !input alert_message
                    data:
                      value: ""

                  # Debug log for cleared/below-threshold alert
                  - condition: template
                    value_template: "{{ debug_enabled }}"
                  - action: logbook.log
                    data:
                      name: Weather Condition Alert
                      message: >-
                        Alert CLEARED or below threshold: {{ matching_count }} matching
                        hour(s) in the next {{ hours_to_check }} hour(s) for conditions {{ conds }}.
                      entity_id: !input weather_entity

            # 3) Default: no hourly forecast data -> do nothing to helpers, optional debug
            default:
              - condition: template
                value_template: "{{ debug_enabled }}"
              - action: logbook.log
                data:
                  name: Weather Condition Alert
                  message: >
                    No hourly forecast data available; alert state left unchanged.
                  entity_id: !input weather_entity

    # Default branch of top-level choose: not our interval -> skip, optional debug
    default:
      - condition: template
        value_template: "{{ debug_enabled }}"
      - action: logbook.log
        data:
          name: Weather Condition Alert
          message: >
            Interval check skipped this run (current interval setting does not match).
          entity_id: !input weather_entity
